1
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:29,950
[The Story of Xing Fu]

2
00:01:30,050 --> 00:01:32,950
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:35,879 --> 00:01:36,519
Security guard?

4
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,799
Does it mean that I have to guard the doors?

5
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:41,920
Qinglai.

6
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,840
It's not like any other security guard job.

7
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:45,560
Yani's father

8
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,120
spoke to the department of safety and security
of their company

9
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,519
and begged them

10
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,640
to make you the security guard
at the Municipal Council.

11
00:01:51,599 --> 00:01:53,159
That's where your father-in-law works.

12
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:54,200
Precisely.

13
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:55,040
Qinglai.

14
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:55,640
You

15
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:57,000
will be serving the country.

16
00:01:59,439 --> 00:02:00,079
From now on,

17
00:02:00,079 --> 00:02:01,480
you'll be a public servant.

18
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,120
Oh!

19
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,599
I should've guessed it.

20
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:08,080
He's the director
of the Organization Department.

21
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,360
There's nothing he can't do

22
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,439
as long as he wants to.

23
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,120
Sure.

24
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:13,960
That's nice.

25
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:16,599
Then...

26
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:17,879
About that...

27
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:18,599
I mean...

28
00:02:18,599 --> 00:02:19,360
How much

29
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,280
will I be earning

30
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,159
every month?

31
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,639
I guess

32
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,599
slightly over 2,000 yuan.

33
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,400
Slightly over 2,000 yuan?

34
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,159
Wait.

35
00:02:27,199 --> 00:02:27,800
I'm going

36
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:28,520
to work

37
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:29,039
for the government.

38
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:30,280
Is that all I'm going to get?

39
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,680
That's quite a lot.

40
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:34,280
I only earn 1,500 yuan a month.

41
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,879
How can you compare yourself to me?

42
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,080
I'm a man.

43
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,680
I have to earn more than you.

44
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:40,639
Qinglai.

45
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:42,879
I hold a master's degree

46
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:44,919
and I only earn slightly over 3,000 yuan a month.

47
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,039
If you were to find another job yourself,

48
00:02:47,039 --> 00:02:47,599
you probably wouldn't

49
00:02:47,599 --> 00:02:49,159
be able to land yourself such a good offer.

50
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:50,159
Right?

51
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,560
Moreover,

52
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,759
if you join the public service,

53
00:02:52,879 --> 00:02:54,240
they will provide you with
five social insurance and one housing fund.

54
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,319
Your future will be guaranteed.

55
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:56,759
Qinglai.

56
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:58,159
We need to be grateful.

57
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:58,680
Right.

58
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,439
Grateful.

59
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:01,479
Grateful.

60
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:03,120
I'm always grateful.

61
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:04,360
Sure.

62
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:07,560
Then...

63
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,280
Extend

64
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,639
my gratitude to your father-in-law.

65
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:10,560
Yeah.

66
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,719
Extend our gratitude to Yani's dad.

67
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,120
Don't worry.

68
00:03:13,479 --> 00:03:14,639
I will make sure to send your word to him.

69
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,159
Sure.

70
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,080
I will be

71
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,199
a public servant.

72
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:57,800
Xingfu.

73
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,599
Where is the photocopy paper?

74
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,800
Where did you keep them?

75
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,680
It's right here.

76
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,479
-Thanks.
-We're only left with these.

77
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,520
It's time we restock.

78
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,639
It'll be cheaper if we buy more.

79
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:14,039
Don't throw away the used papers.

80
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,039
I've organized them

81
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,879
and placed them here.

82
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,600
I've put all the papers here,

83
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,560
so I can place it

84
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,480
under my lunchbox.

85
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,319
Wait.

86
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,120
You want to place this under your lunchbox?

87
00:04:26,279 --> 00:04:27,680
Didn't you say that we should be thrifty?

88
00:04:28,079 --> 00:04:29,160
You said that the business

89
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:29,920
has been slow

90
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,199
and told us to work hard and be more frugal.

91
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:33,399
You also mentioned...

92
00:04:33,879 --> 00:04:34,480
Tight...

93
00:04:35,279 --> 00:04:36,279
Tight...

94
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:36,680
Money...

95
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:37,319
Politics?

96
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,879
Tight monetary policy.

97
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,160
Tight monetary policy.

98
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:41,879
Ms. Xingfu.

99
00:04:42,079 --> 00:04:43,360
You're neither practicing
tight monetary policy,

100
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,399
nor being frugal.

101
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,959
You're just wasting resources.

102
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,079
Wasting resources?

103
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:49,199
Look.

104
00:04:49,199 --> 00:04:49,839
Tell you what.

105
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,399
Take this photocopy paper for an example.

106
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,120
You can use both sides.

107
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,040
You can flip it

108
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,199
and use the other side.

109
00:04:56,439 --> 00:04:56,839
Look.

110
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,240
Place it in there,

111
00:04:58,279 --> 00:04:59,120
and you can use it again.

112
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,199
I see.

113
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:02,879
Be careful.

114
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,360
Doing this

115
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,000
is good for both the environment and our wallets.

116
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:08,800
It'll be very wasteful

117
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,079
to place the paper under your lunchbox.

118
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,399
Moreover, if you really want to place something
under your lunchbox,

119
00:05:11,399 --> 00:05:12,720
can't you just use

120
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,439
the free newspaper?

121
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:15,000
You're just...

122
00:05:15,439 --> 00:05:15,959
Fine.

123
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:16,639
You're just...

124
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,199
How do I put this?

125
00:05:17,199 --> 00:05:18,120
You won't know how expensive the essentials are

126
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,680
when you're not the one who pays for them.

127
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,319
I got it.

128
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,839
I won't place them under my lunchbox again.

129
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,560
I got it.

130
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:25,720
Don't...

131
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,360
Don't pass out here.

132
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,160
I'm feeling really dizzy right now.

133
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:27,759
Hang in there.

134
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:28,920
I'll get you water.

135
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:37,920
Have some water.

136
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:38,800
Thank you.

137
00:05:40,399 --> 00:05:41,319
I have something to tell you.

138
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,600
I would like to take a half-day off tomorrow.

139
00:05:44,439 --> 00:05:45,000
I'll be doing

140
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,120
some property viewings tomorrow.

141
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,040
I don't want to keep living
under someone else's roof.

142
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:49,240
Go ahead.

143
00:05:50,199 --> 00:05:50,600
Okay.

144
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,240
Xingfu.

145
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,439
You're too extravagant.

146
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,360
These disposable cups

147
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,959
are meant for clients.

148
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,240
We should all just use

149
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,519
our own mugs.

150
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,560
Do you know how much one of these costs?

151
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,040
How much?

152
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,519
Too much.

153
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,199
Fine. I got it.

154
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:10,360
What are you doing?

155
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:10,839
I...

156
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,480
Let me clean it.

157
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:14,240
Are you going to let the clients reuse this?

158
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,759
That's very unhygienic.

159
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:17,879
Don't do it again.

160
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,160
Sure.

161
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,319
Wait.

162
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,639
Since I've used this,

163
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,279
I should drink more.

164
00:06:47,839 --> 00:06:48,399
Isn't this cap

165
00:06:48,439 --> 00:06:49,839
a little too big?

166
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:50,839
Not at all.

167
00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:52,000
It fits you perfectly.

168
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,160
It's as if it was custom-made for you.

169
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:54,279
Qinglai.

170
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,560
You are born to wear this uniform.

171
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:58,759
Everyone will fear you

172
00:06:58,759 --> 00:07:00,240
when you're standing at the gate
with this fierce look.

173
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,360
That's not true.

174
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,879
You addressed Mr. Xu as your uncle

175
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:05,680
when he came in the other day.

176
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,079
That's when I learned about the truth.

177
00:07:08,519 --> 00:07:09,279
What truth?

178
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,319
Like uncle,

179
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,639
like nephew.

180
00:07:15,639 --> 00:07:16,360
What are you trying to say?

181
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,399
Qinglai, listen to me.

182
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:21,600
Tang Sanzang went through 81 challenges

183
00:07:21,639 --> 00:07:22,680
before he could bring back
the Buddhist Scriptures.

184
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:23,279
Look at me.

185
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,199
I'm only a security guard,

186
00:07:24,439 --> 00:07:25,639
but I have to go through many challenges as well.

187
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,319
First of all, there's the training,

188
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:27,920
then the examination,

189
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:28,839
and then the assessment.

190
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,759
It took me a lot of effort.

191
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:31,199
I'm not like you.

192
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,800
It must be nice having connections.

193
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,199
I don't have

194
00:07:36,199 --> 00:07:37,160
any connections.

195
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:38,120
I don't.

196
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:39,839
You know Mr. Xu.

197
00:07:39,839 --> 00:07:40,879
Isn't that a connection?

198
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:42,519
Qinglai.

199
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:43,959
From now on, I, Song Xiaoshan,

200
00:07:43,959 --> 00:07:44,879
will obey you.

201
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,360
I'll run errands for you.

202
00:07:46,879 --> 00:07:47,800
I'll do everything you say,

203
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,279
so please take care of me.

204
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,160
Mr. Xu,

205
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:54,759
you have a meeting at 2 PM later.

206
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:56,920
All the departments are ready

207
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:57,879
to report their work to you.

208
00:07:58,839 --> 00:08:00,399
Bring Wang and Li with you.

209
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:01,839
Also...

210
00:08:01,879 --> 00:08:02,360
Also...

211
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,360
Mr. Sun.

212
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:04,120
He'll lead all the members

213
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,240
to go through the whole thing again.

214
00:08:06,279 --> 00:08:07,759
The smaller the matter is,
the more careful we should be.

215
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:08,519
You're right.

216
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:10,079
Qinglai.

217
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:11,920
Wasn't that Mr. Xu?

218
00:08:13,319 --> 00:08:13,759
Yes.

219
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,079
Why didn't you

220
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:16,040
say hi to him?

221
00:08:17,839 --> 00:08:19,079
He was working.

222
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,759
We have nothing important to tell him, right?

223
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,199
Skipping a hi won't hurt.

224
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,000
We should say hi

225
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,639
when it's necessary.

226
00:08:27,279 --> 00:08:33,500
[Security]

227
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:38,679
Sir,

228
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:39,879
do you think

229
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,360
you can offer me a cheaper rate?

230
00:08:41,519 --> 00:08:42,399
How cheap are you expecting?

231
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:43,759
What about 600 yuan?

232
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,679
600 yuan?

233
00:08:44,759 --> 00:08:46,039
That's very bold of you.

234
00:08:46,279 --> 00:08:46,919
Tell you what.

235
00:08:47,039 --> 00:08:47,799
This is the cheapest I can offer

236
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:49,320
for this house.

237
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,559
1,000 yuan.

238
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,279
But this place is so far from the city center.

239
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:52,799
Far?

240
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:53,679
You get fresh air here.

241
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,279
You can go for a jog in the morning.

242
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,200
Exercise

243
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:56,960
can make you healthier.

244
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,080
Jogging

245
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,440
is quite time-consuming.

246
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:00,399
What about this?

247
00:09:00,639 --> 00:09:01,879
Why don't you rent it to me?

248
00:09:02,679 --> 00:09:03,120
And I...

249
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,720
I'll clean the place for you.

250
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:05,960
Clean the place?

251
00:09:06,919 --> 00:09:08,559
I'm renting a house,

252
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:10,039
not hiring a housekeeper.

253
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,000
What about this?

254
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:12,000
Why don't you

255
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:12,919
try somewhere else?

256
00:09:21,759 --> 00:09:22,120
Hey.

257
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:22,919
Li.

258
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,200
Yes. I can hear you.

259
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:24,960
Go ahead.

260
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:44,960
My goodness.

261
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,120
Sir.

262
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:04,039
Are you all right?

263
00:10:04,039 --> 00:10:04,559
Sir.

264
00:10:04,679 --> 00:10:05,320
Sir.

265
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,720
Sir, are you all right?

266
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,000
Sir.

267
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,480
Are you okay, sir?

268
00:10:16,679 --> 00:10:18,519
I think my legs are stuck.

269
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:19,360
I can't get them out.

270
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:21,639
Can you call an ambulance for me?

271
00:10:21,879 --> 00:10:22,360
Sure.

272
00:10:27,399 --> 00:10:27,879
Hey.

273
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:28,960
Is this 120?

274
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:30,679
There is a car crash here

275
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,240
at Dongrun Road, the old town.

276
00:10:32,759 --> 00:10:33,440
The driver is stuck

277
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,799
and he can't get out of his car.

278
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:36,240
Yes, he's conscious.

279
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:37,960
He can articulate.

280
00:10:40,279 --> 00:10:40,799
Okay.

281
00:10:41,559 --> 00:10:42,679
Please come here as soon as possible.

282
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:52,559
Hey.

283
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,519
110?

284
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,159
There's a car crash here

285
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,600
at Dongrun Road, the old town.

286
00:10:59,159 --> 00:10:59,759
The door is stuck

287
00:10:59,759 --> 00:11:00,879
right now.

288
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:02,360
Someone is injured.

289
00:11:04,559 --> 00:11:05,360
Car plate number?

290
00:11:08,399 --> 00:11:10,080
Wan X6C073.

291
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:12,799
Sure.

292
00:11:13,879 --> 00:11:14,159
Then,

293
00:11:14,159 --> 00:11:15,480
I'll be waiting for you right here.

294
00:11:16,159 --> 00:11:16,799
Sure.

